{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "In this report we summarize the most recent results of measurements of the angle \u03b3/\u03c6 3 of the Unitarity Triangle.",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "INTRODUCTION",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Measurements of the Unitarity Triangle parameters allow to search for New Physics effects at low energies. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "One angle, \u03c6 1 (or \u03b2 ) 1 , has been measured with high precision at BaBar and Belle experiments, the B factories operated at the e + e \u2212 colliders with the center-of-mass energy at \u03d2(4S) resonance. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 23,
                    "end": 24,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "1"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 78,
                    "end": 83,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w0"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The measurements of the angle \u03c6 2 /\u03b1 is more difficult due to theoretical uncertainties in the calculation of the penguin diagram contribution. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Precise determination of the third angle, \u03c6 3 /\u03b3, is possible, e.g., in the decays B \u00b1 \u2192 DK \u00b1 . ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Although it is theoretically clean due to the absence of loop contributions, it requires a lot more data than for the other angles. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "This report summarizes the most recent progress in measuring the angle \u03c6 3 /\u03b3.",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The theoretically clean measurement technique was suggested by Gronau, London, and Wyler (GLW). ",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "It exploits the interference between B \u2212 \u2192 D 0 K \u2212 and B \u2212 \u2192D 0 K \u2212 decay amplitudes, where the D 0 andD 0 mesons decay to the same CP eigenstate (CP-even [1]. ",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 155,
                    "end": 158,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The following variables are used to extract \u03c6 3 using the GLW method: the asymmetries",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "and the ratios ",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "is the ratio of the b \u2192 c\u016bs and b \u2192 ucs magnitudes, \u03b4 B is their strong-phase difference. ",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "It can also be expressed in terms of three independent quantities:",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Recently, BaBar updated their GLW analysis using the data sample of 382M BB pairs [2]. ",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 82,
                    "end": 85,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "These results are presented in Table 1. ",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 31,
                    "end": 38,
                    "type": "table",
                    "ref_id": "tab_0",
                    "text": "Table 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Also results from Belle using 275M BB pairs are shown [3].",
            "section": "GLW ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 54,
                    "end": 57,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "[3]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 18,
                    "end": 23,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "ADS METHOD",
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The difficulties in the application of the GLW methods arise primarily due to the small magnitude of the CP asymmetry of the B + \u2192 D CP K + decay probabilities, which may lead to significant systematic uncertainties in the observation of the CP violation. ",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "An alternative approach was proposed by Atwood, Dunietz and Soni [4]. ",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 65,
                    "end": 68,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[4]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Instead of using the D 0 decays to CP eigenstates, the ADS method uses Cabibbo-favored and doubly Cabibbo-suppressed decays:D \u2192 K \u2212 \u03c0 + and D 0 \u2192 K \u2212 \u03c0 + . ",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "In the decays",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": ", the suppressed B decay corresponds to the Cabibbo-allowed D 0 decay, and vice versa. ",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Therefore, the interfering amplitudes are of similar magnitudes, and one can expect the significant CP asymmetry.",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Unfortunately, the branching ratios of the decays mentioned above are so small that they cannot be observed using the current experimental statistics. ",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The observable that is measured in the ADS method is the fraction of the suppressed and allowed branching ratios:",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "where r D is the ratio of the doubly Cabibbo-suppressed and Cabibbo-allowed D 0 decay amplitudes:",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "and \u03b4 is a sum of strong phase differences in B and D decays: The update of the ADS analysis using 657M BB pairs is reported by Belle [5]. ",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 134,
                    "end": 137,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 128,
                    "end": 133,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In the absence of the signal the ratio of the suppressed and allowed modes is measured to be: R ADS < 1.8 \u00d7 10 \u22122 at 90% C.L., which corresponds to r B < 0.19.",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Recently, the ADS analysis has been performed by BaBar using B 0 \u2192 D 0 K * 0 decay modes with D 0 \u2192 K \u2212 \u03c0 + , K \u2212 \u03c0 + \u03c0 0 or K \u2212 \u03c0 + \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 , based on 465M BB events [6]. ",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 167,
                    "end": 170,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "[6]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Neglecting K * 0 final state interference and combining three D 0 decay modes the 95% probability range for r S is found to be:",
            "section": "ADS METHOD",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "A Dalitz plot analysis of a D meson three-body final state allows to obtain all the information required for a \u03c6 3 determination. ",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "Three-body final states such as K 0 S \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 [7,8] have been suggested as promising modes for the extraction of \u03c6 3 . ",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 46,
                    "end": 49,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "[7,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 49,
                    "end": 51,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "8]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Like GLW or ADS method, the two amplitudes interfere as the D 0 andD 0 mesons decay into the same final state K 0 S \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 . ",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "Once the D 0 \u2192 K 0 S \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 decay amplitude, f D , is known, a simultaneous fit of B + and B \u2212 data allows the contributions of r B , \u03c6 3 and \u03b4 B to be separated.",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "Both Belle and BaBar collaborations reported recently the updates of the \u03c6 3 /\u03b3 measurements using Dalitz plot analysis. ",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 5,
                    "end": 10,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The preliminary results obtained by Belle [9] uses the data sample of 657M BB pairs and two modes, B \u00b1 \u2192 DK \u00b1 and B \u00b1 \u2192 D * K \u00b1 with D * \u2192 D\u03c0 0 . ",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 42,
                    "end": 45,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[9]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 36,
                    "end": 41,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The neutral D meson is reconstructed in K 0 S \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 final state in both cases. ",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The f D is determined from a large sample of flavor-tagged D 0 \u2192 K 0 S \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 decays produced in continuum e + e \u2212 annihilation.",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "BaBar uses a smaller data sample of 383M BB pairs [10], but analyses seven different decay modes: B \u00b1 \u2192 DK \u00b1 , B \u00b1 \u2192 D * K \u00b1 with D * \u2192 D\u03c0 0 and D\u03b3, and B \u00b1 \u2192 DK * \u00b1 , where the neutral D meson is reconstructed in K 0 S \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 and K 0 S K + K \u2212 (except for B \u00b1 \u2192 DK * \u00b1 ) final states. ",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 50,
                    "end": 54,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "[10]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The K-matrix formalism is used by default to describe the \u03c0\u03c0 S-wave, while the K\u03c0 S-wave is parametrized using K * 0 (1430) resonances and as effective range non-resonant component with a phase shift.",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The results of both analyses are summarized in Table 2.",
            "section": "DALITZ PLOT ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 47,
                    "end": 54,
                    "type": "table",
                    "ref_id": "tab_1",
                    "text": "Table 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "B 0 \u2192 D * \u2212 \u03c0 + ANALYSES",
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The study of the time-dependent decay rates of B 0 (B 0 ) \u2192 D * \u2213 \u03c0 \u00b1 provides a theoretically clean method for extracting sin(2\u03c6 1 +\u03c6 3 ) from the interference of doubly Cabibbosuppressed (DCS) b \u2192 u and Cabibbo-favored (CF) b \u2192 c amplitudes. ",
            "section": "B 0 \u2192 D * \u2212 \u03c0 + ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The CP violation",
            "section": "B 0 \u2192 D * \u2212 \u03c0 + ANALYSES",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "TABLE 1 .",
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "Results of the GLW analyses \u22120.09 \u00b1 0.09 \u00b1 0.02 \u22120.12 \u00b1 0.14 \u00b1 0.05 x + \u22120.09 \u00b1 0.05 \u00b1 0.02 \u22120.06 \u00b1 0.08 \u00b1 0.05",
            "section": "TABLE 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "where \u03b4 \u2032 = \u03b4 B for D 1 and \u03b4 B + \u03c0 for D 2 and r B",
            "section": "TABLE 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "TABLE 2 .",
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "Results of the Dalitz plot analyses BaBar Belle \u03c6 3 /\u03b3 76 +23 \u221224 o \u00b1 5 o \u00b1 5 o (3.0\u03c3 CPV) 76 +12 \u221213 o \u00b1 4 o \u00b1 9 o (3.5\u03c3 CPV) r B 0.086 \u00b1 0.035 \u00b1 0.010 \u00b1 0.011 0.16 \u00b1 0.04 \u00b1 0.01 \u00b1 0.05 r * B 0.135 \u00b1 0.051 \u00b1 0.011 \u00b1 0.005 0.21 \u00b1 0.08 \u00b1 0.01 \u00b1 0.05",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 8,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 42,
                    "end": 47,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Two different notations of the Unitarity Triangle are used: \u03b1, \u03b2 , \u03b3 or \u03c6 2 , \u03c6 1 and \u03c6 3 , respectively.",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "parameters are given by",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "where \u03b4 is the strong phase difference between DCS and CF decays. ",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "Since the ratio R of these two amplitudes is small, \u2248 0.02 [11], the amount of CP violation is expected to be small and a large data sample is needed in order to obtain sufficient sensitivity.",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 10,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 59,
                    "end": 63,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b11",
                    "text": "[11]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Recently, Belle updated their result using 657M BB pairs data sample with a partial reconstruction technique, wherein the signal is distinguished from background on the basis of kinematics of the 'fast' pion (\u03c0 f ) from B \u2192 D * \u03c0 f , and the 'soft' pion (\u03c0 s ) from the subsequent decay of D * \u2192 D\u03c0 s ; the D meson is not reconstructed at all [12]. ",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 10,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 343,
                    "end": 347,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b12",
                    "text": "[12]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 10,
                    "end": 15,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w6"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "To suppressed the increased background a high momentum lepton is required in the event. ",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "This lepton also provides the information about the flavor and decay vertex of the tagging B meson, which is necessary for the time-dependent analysis. ",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "The vertex of the signal B is reconstructed using 'fast' pion only. ",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "The fit results using the partial reconstruction method are: ",
            "section": "TABLE 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "CONCLUSION",
            "section_rank": 11
        },
        {
            "text": "In the past year, many new measurements of angle \u03c6 3 /\u03b3 are provided by Belle and BaBar. ",
            "section": "CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 11,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 72,
                    "end": 77,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Belle",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w7"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The most precise measurements are performed using Dalitz plot analyses of B \u2192 DK decays in a good agreement between both experiments.",
            "section": "CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 11
        }
    ]
}